            <p>
               <choice corresp="#a1">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [27d] ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #a7 #a8 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6 #b7 #b8">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1949"/><citedRange>II, 68-70</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a2">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... surely he falls deeply ...</seg></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... bestimmt fällt der tief ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... surely he falls deeply ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>105</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a3">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>78</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... entirely [lit. without remainder]. All lives ... [28d] ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a4">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (at) the great king’s death ... [29d] ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a5">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... There came Saṃghatrāta [his] teacher ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a6">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... I let rain the rain of tears ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a6 #a7">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>673</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a7">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... you (sg.) ... . See my body! Force ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a8">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the old fighters, the heroes ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b1">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>181</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in the fetter of death. [31d]</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b2">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>716</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... unhappy one and when will I obtain...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b3">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">[32d] Now give up all other imaginations! ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b4">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... sons, the queen, governance, without ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b4 #b5">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">If you now give up all, [your] lands, villages, women, sons, queen, nay, [and your] countless possessions, [your] district kings and likewise [your] ministers, then you will now go, lead by your own deeds, to the other world.  (cf : ii, 68–69)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>671</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b5">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1979b"/><citedRange>55</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... now (go to) the other world! [33d]</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b6">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... keeping apart, in a moment the (wind) ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b6 #b7">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">[Just] as when the animals are dwelling together, the night will grow light, but, when (the animals) are dwelling apart, in an instant the wind scatters them, so pay attention to your relatives! As long as you will be friendly …, [but] as soon as life leaves your body, they will all be alien to you.  (cf : ii, 69; 23–24)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>673</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b7">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... this body, they (will) all soon (become as) strangers ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b8">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the attach(ments) to one’s own pe(ople) ...</seg></seg>
               </choice>
            </p>
